latestPosts.caption:
No one talks about these until it’s too late. If you want stunning, regret-free wedding photos — read this before your big day.

📌 Not sharing a shot list with your photographer.

📌 Rushing through your couple portraits post-ceremony.

📌 Letting guests block the view during bridal/groom entries.

📌 Not doing a quick trial of your bridal entry walk.

📌 Skipping a solo shot with your parents or siblings.

📌 Ignoring the background for your getting-ready pictures.

📌 Wearing your dupatta before makeup fully sets.

📌 Not assigning someone to coordinate 
family group photos.

📌 Not asking for candid moments during rituals.

📌 Skipping post-ceremony candid shots with just the two of you.

📌 Forgetting to get a picture with your best friends.

📌 Not briefing your photographer about emotional moments to look out for (like bidaai or first look).

📌 Letting family/friends interrupt during couple portraits.

📌 Not getting your entry captured from both front and back angles.

📌 Skipping close-ups of your hands during rituals (mehendi + jewelry shots).

📌 Not capturing a full-length photo before guests arrive or rituals begin.
.
.
.
.
